Categorical UNRELATED values

One-Hot Encoding 
Original
Name Color          Name Red green blue
Pikachu red          Pikachu   1     0       0
Dracula blue       Dracula    0     0       1
Attila Green          Attila        0     1        0
Robin Green        Robin       0      1        0

Optimized-> (n-1) classes [ red, green] -> 0 0 indicated blue!
Name Color          Name Red green 
Pikachu red          Pikachu   1     0       
Dracula blue       Dracula    0     0       
Attila Green          Attila        0     1       
Robin Green        Robin        0     1        

Use case-> 
1. Generalizing the model.
                1.  w1* pikachu + w2* 1 + w3* 0 +b = y
                2. For values with green or blue, feature val =0!
2. FILTERING-> 3 separate models for where -> red==1, green==1, red==0 && green==0



Label Binarizing- 

One hot encoding of LABEL not the feature!
Instead of separate columns, we build a MATRIX!

Label Binarizing is preferred way of exporting the classes predicted by the model, along with the model!

Y -> Cat/Dog/Koala/Giraffe

Binarized -> cat -> [1 0 0 ], dog -> [0 1 0], koala-> [0 0 1], Giraffe -> [0 0 0]

Label encoding/ One hot encoding-> features
Label Binarizing -> Output Labels!

